/-
PhiPsiCoprime.lean тАФ own work for the Fermat project.

The direct coprimality of the division polynomials `╬жтВЩ` and `╬иSqтВЩ`
over a field with `╬Ф тЙа 0`, replacing the resultant-formula node. A
common root over the algebraic closure lifts to a curve point whose
`╧И`-values form a normalised EDS with `wтВБ = 1`; `╬иSq`-vanishing gives
`wтВЩ = 0`, `╬ж`-vanishing gives `wтВЩтВКтВБ wтВЩтВЛтВБ = 0` (through the definition
`╬жтВЩ = X ╬иSqтВЩ тИТ pre╬итВЩтВКтВБ pre╬итВЩтВЛтВБ тмЭ parity` and the on-curve identity
`╬итВВSq(xтВА) = ╧ИтВВ(P)┬▓`), so the rank of apparition divides two
consecutive integers тАФ impossible тАФ unless the rank has adjacent
zeros, which forces the degenerate seeds `(╧ИтВВ, ╧ИтВГ) = (0,0)` or
`(╧ИтВГ, ╧ИтВД) = (0,0)`, excluded by the small B├йzout certificates
`F тмЭ ╬итВВSq + G тмЭ ╬итВГ = тИТ╬Ф┬▓` and `F тмЭ ╬итВГ + G тмЭ pre╬итВД = ╬ФтБ┤`.
-/
